abstract: Chani Nicholas doesn’t want to tell you who you are, but who you can be.
snippet: Chani Nicholas doesn’t want to tell you who you are, but who you can be.
lead_paragraph: The first time I met up with the astrologer Chani Nicholas in Los Angeles, in December, it was for a lunch interview. We sipped our drinks and chewed truffle French fries; I asked questions and she answered them. The conversation flowed easily. We laughed a lot.

abstract: There hasn’t been a single poll in weeks that could help the Democratic presidential candidates qualify for the next debate. The party blames the polling organizations.
snippet: There hasn’t been a single poll in weeks that could help the Democratic presidential candidates qualify for the next debate. The party blames the polling organizations.
lead_paragraph: NORTH CONWAY, N.H. — The morning after the Democrats’ last debate in December, the Democratic National Committee announced the thresholds to qualify for the next one, scheduled for Jan. 14 in Des Moines: 5 percent support in four qualifying polls, or 7 percent in two early-state polls. With those steeper requirements in place, just five candidates have qualified so far: Joe Biden, Bernie Sanders, Elizabeth Warren, Pete Buttigieg and Amy Klobuchar.

headline_main: D.N.C. Tells Pollsters to Do More Polls

abstract: Senator Amy Klobuchar’s campaign announced raising $11.4 million in the fourth quarter of 2019, and Senator Cory Booker said he brought in $6.6 million.
snippet: Senator Amy Klobuchar’s campaign announced raising $11.4 million in the fourth quarter of 2019, and Senator Cory Booker said he brought in $6.6 million.
lead_paragraph: HANOVER, N.H. — Senator Amy Klobuchar of Minnesota raised $11.4 million in the fourth quarter of 2019, her campaign announced on Friday, a sum that was more than twice what she collected during the prior three months but still left her no better than sixth in fund-raising for the last three months among Democrats running for president.
